content:
Add Filters to Explore Tableau Views

Add filters to explore Tableau content and unlock additional insights.

Required Editions: Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, available with CRM Analytics in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions, and Developer Edition.

Select the Tableau view and click the Parameter tab. Click Add Parameter. Click Filter Field and select a Tableau dimension field as the filter. Add a name to Parameter Name. Click Value Type then specify how to use values for the filter.

To add static values, select Static and type in the text field. To filter values using a CRM Analytics dashboard filter, select Dynamic and link it to the Tableau view.

To filter an array of values, separate each value with a comma, then click Use values in an array. To update the view as needed by customer segment, create a custom query filter and set up a dynamic parameter that links the filter to the Tableau view.

See also: CRM Analytics Dashboard JSON Overview
title: Adding Filters to Tableau Views in CRM Analytics
